<ItacAcademyItem AcademyId="0019" RecordId="021-000001473"><Name>Filarmonica (Accademia)</Name><AlternativeName>Floridi (Accademia dei - 1615)|Filomusi (Accademia dei - 1622)|Filaschisi (Accademia dei 1633)</AlternativeName><City CityId="1"><CityItalianName>Bologna</CityItalianName><CityEnglishName>Bologna</CityEnglishName><CityLatinName>Bononiae</CityLatinName></City><EmblemDescription>Organ</EmblemDescription><Motto>Unitate melos</Motto><StartDate>1615</StartDate><EndDate>still active today</EndDate><DateText>1615-still active today</DateText><Notes>These were four Academies with a special interest for music in seventeenth century Bologna: Accademia dei Floridi was created in 1615 by Adriano Banchieri. This was followed by Accademia dei Filomusi, created by Girolamo Giacobbi in 1622 (motto: `Vocis dulcedine captant` and Pan`s pipes as an emblem). This was continued by the Accademia dei Filaschisi, created in 1633 by Domenico Brunetti and Francesco Bertacchi (motto: `Orbem demulcet attactu`, and David`s harp as an amblem). Subsequently the Accademia Filarmonica was created in 1666, and is still existing. Publications related to these Academies, but not in British Library collections, are: Alberto Bertelli, Siringa fugace, favoletta in musica; rappresentata nell`accademia de` Filomusi di Bologna da Alberto Bertelli l`inutile... (In Bologna: presso Clemente Ferroni, 1628); Amor tiranno accademia fatta in casa dell`illustrissimo sig. senator Fantuzzi composta in musica da Domenico Pellegrini accad. Filomuso all`illustrissima signora Sulpizia Orsi Grimaldi (Bologna, Dozza, 1649); 
Florimi, Giovanni Andrea, Hymni unica voce concinendi cum instromentis ... a fratre Joanne Andrea Florimieiusdem ordinis.In Senarum metropolitana musices moderatori,et Accademico Concertato (Opus Quartum Bononiae: typis Iacobi Montii, 1673); Florimi, Giovanni Andrea, Flores melliflui in Deiparae Virginis cum octo plenis vocibus concinendi F. Io. Andreae Florimi senensis in metropolitana Senarum musices vice praefecti et accademici Concertati Io. Vincentio Luchesinio dicati: opus quintum (Bononiae : typis Iacobi Montii, 1676); Florimi, Giovanni Andrea, Versi della turba concertati a quattro voci per li Passij della domenica delle Palme e venerd&#236; santo con alcuni brevi e devoti Motetti da cantarsi nel visitare li Santissimi Sepolcri : opera settima / Dedicati agl`illustrissimi Dignit&#224; e Canonici del insigni cattedrale di Pistoia del padre Gio. Andrea Florimi maestro di capella dell`istessa,et Accademico Concertato (Bologna: Giacomo Monti, 1682); 

In the notes field of many academicians I have reported the date when they joined the Accademia Filarmonica, and their city of provenance (after Laura Callegari Hill). 
Bibliography:
Giuseppe Vecchi, Le Accademie musicali del primo seicento e Monteverdi a Bologna (Bologna: A.M.I.S., 1969); Nestore Morini, L`Accademia Filarmonica di Bologna, 1666-1966, vol. I, Fondazione e vicende storiche (Bologna, 1967); Laura Callegari Hill, L`Accademia Filarmonica di Bologna, 1666-1800 (Bologna, 1991).</Notes><ItacPersonItem PersonId="5085" RecordId="022-000000082"><Name>Giacobbi, Girolamo , , 1567-1628</Name><Nickname>Academico Filomuso</Nickname><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7707" RecordId="022-000001482"><Name>Vernizzi , Ottavio , , </Name><Nickname>L`Indefesso</Nickname><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7708" RecordId="022-000001483"><Name>Manzoli , Domenico, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7709" RecordId="022-000001484"><Name>Monteverdi , Claudio, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7710" RecordId="022-000001485"><Name>Guerra, Bartolomeo, , </Name><Nickname>Il Sollevato</Nickname><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7711" RecordId="022-000001486"><Name>Bonini, Francesco, , </Name><Nickname>Il Raddolcito</Nickname><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7712" RecordId="022-000001487"><Name>Bertelli, Alberto, , </Name><Nickname>L`Inutile</Nickname><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7713" RecordId="022-000001488"><Name>Consoni, Paolo, , </Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7714" RecordId="022-000001489"><Name>Milani, Francesco, , </Name><Nickname>Il Solitario</Nickname><Motto /><PersonEmblemDescription /></ItacPersonItem><ItacPersonItem PersonId="7715" RecordId="022-000001490"><Name>Cortellini , Camillo, , 1561-1630</Name><Nickname /><Motto /><PersonEmb